Defendant Antonio R Truss in court with attorney Jessica Bellows.  Elizabeth Longo on behalf of Kristin Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
BRANCH 25 FOR BRANCH 40. Case set for sentencing hearing. State placed negotiations on the record. Court ordered the docket be changed to reflect the correct charge the defendant pled to on 5/26/15 and add the "Use of a Dangerous Weapon" modifier. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 2 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 15 MONTHS incarceration, consecutive to COUNT 3;

As to COUNT 3-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive to COUNT 2 AMENDED, credit for 2 days time served. Defendant may have work release and participate in vocational training. Court will allow the defendant to particpate in the Day Reporting Center if eligible. Court will allow the defendant to receive good time.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNT 2 AMENDED and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered 45 days of condition time in the House of Correction, IMPOSED AND STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent;
2) No contact with Ashley L., Michelle L., or any other witnesses to the offense or their residence;
3) Court will allow the defendant to have visitation with his children subject to third party supervision;
4) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges (including the Domestic Abuse Assessment) during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Attend a Batterer's Intervention Program;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on COUNT 3 as it is part of a continuous event;

Defendant to report to the House of Correction to begin the sentence on COUNT 3 on 7/31/15 by 10:00 a.m. 

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds. 

Court ordered bail on deposit to apply to costs, fees and surcharges. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Memorandum of Conditions of Probation;
Sentencing Referral Form;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
